My next chapter starts here. I came out with a podcast called “Let’s Talk” where I open up my heart entirely about losing the love of my life to cancer, and what this whole journey was truly like behind closed doors. This podcast was one of the most inspiring things I could have done for myself during my healing process, as it allowed me to really understand everything that has happened in a way that I couldn’t before. I am so beyond proud of my bravery, and for being able to articulate the story in the way that I do. My next chapter is about showing up to the world, to myself, as my truest authentic self, and speaking from a place of sincere transparency. I am ready to change the way we see the world for the better. Thank you in advance for listening, it is available on Spotify and Apple Podcast. Link in bio

10 years ago today Francesco asked me to be his girlfriend. In one month on March 21st, will be one year that he’s passed away. With that being said, I just wanted to embrace and address all these “firsts” without him. First Christmas without him, first anniversary, first everything. It’s healthy for me to speak on, and acknowledge. For the longest time I wasn’t even able to do that, or get myself to touch social media just to say. So I’ve come a long way. All the “firsts” hit so hard in different ways, and this year as a whole has been such a process. My anniversary is hitting intensely. Been trying to compose myself, and walk myself through the emotions. One hour you are okay, the next hour your body and mind feel like they want to shut down. I really don’t know how else to explain it. I’m still learning how to show up in my present time without getting lost in the past. Grief is just love with no where to go, or maybe it’s love with everywhere to go. And maybe that’s why I just feel you extra today Francesco, and I hope you feel me too.

Recently I was sitting down watching old videos of Francesco and I. I came across these specific clips of him speaking, and couldn’t stop replaying it. It’s like he was channeling all the words that I couldn’t put into sentences of how I been feeling over the last 10 months. I thought it was foreshadowing, and frankly beautiful. The next season of my podcast is called “Finding Inner Peace” but before I start season 2, and take you guys on my inner peace journey, this last video here is for Francesco. It’s what I would say to him if someone brought him back to me for just 1 minute. It’s my goodbye.  Thank you again to everyone who listened to my beautiful love story in season 1, and welcome to finding inner peace

March 21,2022 at 3:05pm I walked in on you right after you took your last breath. I’ll never forget the pain in my body and soul. The emptiness, knowing I’d never hear you speak again. The feeling of wanting God to just take me with you. I remember holding your hand, and giving you a kiss on your forehead the night before, promising you everything was going to be okay. I’m so sorry I wasn’t able to keep that promise. I hope you understand that if I could of took the cancer away from you I would of. One year without you. It doesn’t feel real. Everyday I wake up and keep trying to adjust to my new life. Thank you Francesco for making such an impact on me. No matter how much time goes by, you will always be a piece of me. I am who I am today, because of you. I’ll never forget you.

AHH my first ever interview, in my new studio, with my soul sister. Julia Robinson. My bestfriend sits down with me, and dives into her experience with grief after losing her mother to suicide at the age of 10. She takes us on the journey of what it’s like living without a mother, how she handled it, and how it built her into who she is today. We then dive into my loss, and how she mastered being an amazing support through it all. I am not confident we know how to properly show up for the people we love in this world, and I want to raise awareness to how we could do a better job at being present for those we love. Truthfully, she embodies the definition of a fantastic friend. Blessed to have her on the show, and I hope her story inspires you, as much as it inspired me. OUT NOW on all Podcast platforms!!

My mom bought us tickets to DR, including Francesco before he passed away. It was her gift to him, for his 25th birthday. She told him that when he gets cured, we are ALL going to celebrate him. He deserved it. Once he passed, it was a back and forth decision on whether we were still going to go on behalf of him or not. We decided to still go, because he was such a family man, and we knew he would want us to have an excuse to bond. I never get time with my family, and it ended up being an emotional, but such a beautiful vacation.

The “firsts” are always the most impactful. They hit intensely, and are inescapable. I recommend really using the “firsts” as days to feel and embrace whatever it is your feeling on that day. Let go of any held emotion. Journal, be in nature, be in company, and remember that you are not the only person to go through grief. You are never alone. #griefjourney

I talk on this weeks podcast episode about this Outer Banks trip that I had with my cousins last Easter a month after Francesco passed away. I never had true relationships with my cousins because we do long distance as my parents got divorced. When Francesco passed, they asked me to come spend Easter with them. I was so used to spending holidays with Francesco, that I didn’t know anything else. I was so depressed, but took the risk, and decided to go. It ended up being such an incredible trip. I built relationships with my cousins that I never had, I got to smile and laugh- something I didn’t think would ever be possible after he passed away. It was my first moment in my grief that I found some sort of peace building relationships that I truly always wanted. This trip will always be so special to me, and honestly changed my life.
Some more moments of the beautiful DR trip I took with my family in honor of Fran💞🕊️

When you find ways to keep your loved ones that passed away alive, you come more alive. Even if it means planting a tree in their memory, writing poems, writing letters, lighting a candle, whatever it is- you find those moments to honor them. It’s in these moments that you find peace. It’s so therapeutic and really gives you that reminder that they are always with you. #griefjourney

There’s a point in grief where after you get through the deep depression, the survival guilt, the in-denial stages, you start to reflect. It’s a break through. You start to get tired of suffering, and start to learn how to focus on what you do have, rather than what was taken from you. During my time reflecting one of the major things I realized was that I am still alive. For a long time I forgot that I was, funny enough. When his life was taken, I felt like every single last piece of me went with him. I had to learn to find my purpose again. I had to learn how to live again, and be okay with doing it. So this month I got out of my comfort zone, and have been traveling around Europe. I got to meet his whole Italy family, I stayed in his Italy home, saw his whole hometown, something that him and I always wanted for our relationship. My heart sank meeting his family, because it reminded me that I’ll never get to say “I do” but no matter what, I’ll always get to say I lived a true love story that I’ll seriously never forget for the rest of my life. A beautiful experience in Italy that my heart really needed to entirely heal, and his family told me it was closure for them too. 🥺❤️

P.S the new tattoo on my back “One Life One Chance” was what he had on his arm, so now I carry it on my back❤️

This room was our safe place. Our little escape from the world. After he passed, I used to walk into his room with such pain in my body, but now I stand in the room with a sense of strength. Instead of hating the universe, thanking the universe. Being grateful for every single memory I had with him in this room. Being grateful to say I experienced a love so real. With time, we do find peace, and if there’s anything I want you to get from following me on this grief journey is that you will be okay one day. You will learn to smile again, laugh again, love again… and when you do, you feel so empowered, because you conquered the worst pain you’d ever have to face. A pain that you thought you’d be stuck with forever.  It’s powerful once you get to the other side, and I look forward to the day that you feel what I feel now.

Happy 26th Birthday in heaven Francesco. I watch back these videos over and over just to hear your voice again. I laugh so hard, but while I’m laughing I feel that uncomfortable pit feeling in my stomach where I just feel uneasy. When we were 15 we would sit down and talk for hours on how we wanted our future to look like together. Our kids, our house, our careers. If only our 15 year old selves knew we didn’t have as much time as we dreamed of. God had a bigger and better plan, and wherever you are I just hope you have the biggest smile on your face and are in unconditional peace. I am so blessed that you are out of pain, and I truly hope you are doing all the back flips in the world just like you used to. (He used to land THE CLEANEST back flips on the beach & had so much fun doing it… it was so impressive)❤️ I dream so often to see you again. I can’t wait to see you again. You will always be my number 1. I love you. @cescolopresti

SWIPE for my OFFICIAL 45 hard. Starts tomorrow, January 15th - ends March 1st.😍

If you are joining me I wanted to note:
1. You WILL need a journal, gym membership, and water jug, and a book of choice 💪🏻
2. Your wake up time does NOT need to be the same as mine (8AM) , pick ur time and STICK to it consistently every day. 
3. For food, there is no real diet the overall goal is just make healthier choices. (EX: If you usually go out to eat and get a huge dish of pasta, this month you will challenge yourself to get the roasted chicken with vegetables. )🥕
4. For the gym portion, if you do NOT have experience working out I recommend going on YouTube and looking up workout guides you could follow BUT YOU ARE STILL SHOWING UP AND TRYING🔥perfection is not what’s important, your consistency and dedication to trying is the only thing that matters. (You could also simply do Zumba , yoga, cross fit whatever you are comfortable doing that also moves your body) 
5. I do NOT require working out twice (I know most 75 hards have the 2 workouts per day -I don’t feel that’s necessary. We work smarter, not harder. 
6. Feel free to tag me in your gym pics, your journaling, whatever it is you are documenting. ILL BE WATCHING & SHOWING OFF MY JOURNEY AS WELL🔥

PLEASE feel free to ask questions in the comment section where I will be answering everything-  I’m sure you aren’t the only one who has the same questions. To prove to yourself you have discipline is to prove to yourself you have complete control over your whole existence. To take back control, is to take back your freedom. You will gain confidence, you will gain self awareness, and you will STOP yourself from looping in the same bad habits. To see a change, you need to make a change. Stop crying about how your life isn’t what you want it to be, DO SOMETHING ABOUT IT. See you tomorrow 😎
❤️Stay true to being you. The right ones will align
